Chet,<br><br>
Thanks! Your words are an inspiration and give me hope for that elusive &quot;homecoming&quot; I know I need inside. I am still working on what it is inside that will finally come home! So much of me seems blasted around an unreal landscape at times, I begin to wonder.<br><br>
A total stranger told me today that I had courage to do what I was doing with myself. I also feel good about that, though the process really hurts like hell sometimes. <br><br>
The way to my return is here and at other places with good people who understand. And that Feels Good, too. <br>

